s & Pasta Recipes"],"inLanguage":"en-US","copyrightYear":2020,"copyrightHolder":{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Organization","@id":"https://www.forksoverknives.com/#organization","name":"Forks Over Knives","url":"https://www.forksoverknives.com/","sameAs":[],"logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://www.forksoverknives.com/#logo","inLanguage":"en-US","url":"https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/logo-white.svg?auto=webp","contentUrl":"https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/logo-white.svg?auto=webp","width":169,"height":26,"caption":"Forks Over Knives"},"image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://www.forksoverknives.com/#logo","inLanguage":"en-US","url":"https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/logo-white.svg?auto=webp","contentUrl":"https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/logo-white.svg?auto=webp","width":169,"height":26,"caption":"Forks Over Knives"}},"isAccessibleForFree":true,"articleBody":"Spiced butternut squash blended with nutritional yeast and a little plant milk makes a delightfully rich and “cheesy” sauce for pasta and broccoli. Pumpkin, acorn squash, or delicata squash will also work in this recipe.TipsGluten-free: To make this recipe gluten-free, choose a whole grain gluten-free pasta.Optional Oil: This is a Forks Flex Recipe, which means it includes a small amount of optional oil. If you include the oil, you'll add 40 calories, 5 g total fat, and 1 g saturated fat per serving.Editor's note: Based on reader feedback, we retested this recipe and have reduced the amount of plant-based milk."}]</script><div><div class="bg-cover bg-center bg-no-repeat" style="background-image:url(&quot;https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/butternut-broccoli-mac-and-cheese-wordpress.jpg?auto=webp&quot;)"><div class="container flex h-[420px] items-end justify-start p-5 font-sans max-md:max-w-none md:h-[466px] md:py-6 lg:h-[556px]"><div class="relative w-full bg-white p-5 pt-0 md:max-w-[515px] md:px-8 md:py-7 lg:p-8 lg:pb-7"><div class="left-1/2 top-px bg-white max-md:absolute max-md:w-max max-md:max-w-full max-md:shrink-0 max-md:-translate-x-1/2 max-md:-translate-y-full max-md:px-7 max-md:pb-1 max-md:pt-1.5"><ul class="breadcrumbs flex"><li class="group text-11px uppercase tracking-[1.56px] md:text-sm"><a class="text-fok-navy-500 group-hover:text-fok-teal-600" href="/all-recipes/"><span>Recipes</span></a></li><li class="group text-11px uppercase tracking-[1.56px] md:text-sm"><a class="text-fok-navy-500 group-hover:text-fok-teal-600" href="/recipes/vegan-pasta-noodles/"><span>Vegan Noodles &amp; Pasta Recipes</span></a></li></ul></div><h1 class="mb-4 mt-2 text-[22px] font-bold leading-tight text-fok-navy-500 max-md:text-center md:text-[27px]">Butternut Squash Mac and Cheese with Broccoli</h1><div class="rate-container flex gap-x-10 gap-y-2 max-lg:flex-col max-md:items-center"><a class="flex items-center !text-fok-navy-500" href="#comments-section"><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 !my-0 !pl-0"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><span class="ml-2 flex text-[13px] uppercase leading-[21px] tracking-[1.2px]">(67)</span></a><a class="comments-link group flex items-center" aria-label="Go to comments section" href="#comments-section"><span class="icon-comments text-xl"></span><span class="ml-2 text-sm uppercase text-black hover:text-fok-teal-600">125 Comments</span></a></div></div></div></div><article class="container prose md:prose-lg prose-a:no-underline prose-li:marker:text-black max-md:max-w-none max-md:overflow-hidden lg:mb-16 lg:px-4 lg:pb-6 lg:pt-20 blog:max-w-screen-blog"><div class="article-blocks"><div class="mt-6 max-w-[800px]"><section class="relative max-w-[800px]"><div class="box-post-control mb-6"><ul class="add-info my-0 flex flex-col gap-2.5 !pl-0 font-sans text-[13px] uppercase text-black lg:flex-row"><li class="mr-3 flex w-full items-center text-13px tracking-wide lg:w-auto"><i class="icon-time mr-2 text-21px text-fok-teal-600 lg:text-[27px]"></i><span><span>Prep-time:<!-- --> <time dateTime="P0DT0H30M">30 MINUTES</time> <!-- -->/<!-- --> </span><span>Ready In:<!-- --> <time dateTime="PT1H">1 HOUR</time></span></span></li><li class="mr-3 flex w-full items-center tracking-wide lg:w-auto"><i class="icon-serving mr-2 text-21px text-fok-teal-600 lg:text-[27px]"></i><span>Makes 6 cups</span></li><li class="mr-3 flex w-full items-center tracking-wide lg:w-auto"><i class="icon-serving mr-2 text-21px text-fok-teal-600 lg:text-[27px]"></i><span>Serving size: <!-- -->2 cups</span></li><li class="mr-3 flex w-full items-center tracking-wide lg:w-auto"><a class="popup-print print-recipe-link flex items-center font-sans text-[13px] uppercase !text-black hover:!text-fok-teal-500" href="#"><i class="icon-print text mr-2 text-21px text-fok-teal-600 lg:text-[27px]"></i><span>Print/save recipe</span></a></li></ul></div></section><div class="core-paragraph" data-og-block-area="article-blocks" data-og-block-nth="1" data-og-block-type="core/paragraph" data-raw-html="1"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Spiced butternut squash blended with nutritional yeast and a little plant milk makes a delightfully rich and “cheesy” sauce for pasta and broccoli. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pumpkin, acorn squash, or delicata squash will also work in this recipe.</span></p></div><h2 class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-body1 heading css-l0hvfb" id="h-tips" data-og-block-area="article-blocks" data-og-block-nth="1" data-og-block-type="core/heading" data-rawhtml="1">Tips</h2><div class="core-paragraph" data-og-block-area="article-blocks" data-og-block-nth="2" data-og-block-type="core/paragraph" data-raw-html="1"><p><strong>Gluten-free:</strong> To make this recipe gluten-free, choose a whole grain gluten-free pasta.</p></div><div class="core-paragraph" data-og-block-area="article-blocks" data-og-block-nth="3" data-og-block-type="core/paragraph" data-raw-html="1"><p><strong>Optional Oil:</strong> This is a <a href="https://www.forksoverknives.com/wellness/what-are-forks-flex-recipes-low-oil-optional/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Forks Flex Recipe</a>, which means it includes a small amount of optional oil. If you include the oil, you'll add 40 calories, 5 g total fat, and 1 g saturated fat per serving.</p></div><div class="core-paragraph" data-og-block-area="article-blocks" data-og-block-nth="4" data-og-block-type="core/paragraph" data-raw-html="1"><p><em>Editor's note: Based on reader feedback, we retested this recipe and have reduced the amount of plant-based milk.</em></p></div><div class="not-prose"><div class="mb-6 flex flex-col gap-3 gap-x-12 font-serif text-15px md:flex-row md:gap-6 lg:mb-16"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 md:gap-y-3 gap-x-1 md:gap-x-1"><p class="not-prose">By<!-- --> <a class="text-fok-teal-600 hover:text-fok-teal-500" href="/contributors/darshana-thacker/">Darshana Thacker Wendel</a>,</p><span>Last Updated:<!-- --> <time class="text-fok-navy-500">Jul 4, 2025</time></span></div></div></div><div class="not-prose"><div class="MuiBox-root css-f5x0ou"><div class="MuiBox-root css-1t075fi"><span class="font-sans text-sm uppercase">Share</span><div class="text-xl"><ul class="MuiBox-root css-h4fasg"><li><a class="icon-facebook text-fok-teal-600" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.forksoverknives.com/recipes/vegan-pasta-noodles/butternut-mac-and-cheese-broccoli/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="facebook"></a></li><li><a class="icon-twitter text-fok-teal-600" href="https://twitter.com/share?url=https://www.forksoverknives.com/recipes/vegan-pasta-noodles/butternut-mac-and-cheese-broccoli/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="twitter"></a></li><li><a class="icon-pinterest text-fok-teal-600" href="https://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.forksoverknives.com/recipes/vegan-pasta-noodles/butternut-mac-and-cheese-broccoli/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="pinterest"></a></li><li><a class="icon-mail text-3xl leading-[0] text-fok-teal-600" href="mailto:?subject=Butternut%20Squash%20Mac%20and%20Cheese%20with%20Broccoli&amp;body=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forksoverknives.com%2Frecipes%2Fvegan-pasta-noodles%2Fbutternut-mac-and-cheese-broccoli%2F)" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="mail"></a></li><li class="pb-[2px]"><a class="hover:text-fok-teal- text-fok-teal-600" href="#" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" aria-label="copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="size-5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.666 3.888A2.25 2.25 0 0013.5 2.25h-3c-1.03 0-1.9.693-2.166 1.638m7.332 0c.055.194.084.4.084.612v0a.75.75 0 01-.75.75H9a.75.75 0 01-.75-.75v0c0-.212.03-.418.084-.612m7.332 0c.646.049 1.288.11 1.927.184 1.1.128 1.907 1.077 1.907 2.185V19.5a2.25 2.25 0 01-2.25 2.25H6.75A2.25 2.25 0 014.5 19.5V6.257c0-1.108.806-2.057 1.907-2.185a48.208 48.208 0 011.927-.184"></path></svg></a></li><span class="ml-[-10px] font-sans text-sm leading-[3]">11.8k</span></ul></div></div><div class="flex items-center justify-start gap-x-12 uppercase"><a href="https://my.forksmealplanner.com/login-full?fokrecipeid=8238" target="_blank" data-type="Meal Planner" data-event="add recipe" data-name="Butternut Squash Mac and Cheese with Broccoli"><button class="m-0 whitespace-nowrap px-5 pb-17px pt-19px text-center font-sans text-15px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-slighter transition-colors duration-300 disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:bg-fok-gray-500 disabled:text-fok-gray-600 disabled:hover:bg-fok-gray-500 disabled:hover:text-fok-gray-600 max-sm:whitespace-normal cursor-pointer bg-fok-teal-blue-400 text-fok-navy-500 hover:bg-fok-teal-blue-500 hover:text-white" type="submit">See in Forks Meal Planner</button></a></div></div></div></div><section class="not-prose"><div class="relative"><div class="relative mx-auto max-w-[986px]"><div class="relative z-1 max-w-[723px] pb-24"></div></div><img class="absolute -bottom-16 right-[-33px] -z-1 max-md:bottom-[-30px] max-md:right-[-100px] max-md:w-[230px] max-sm:bottom-[-137px]" src="/images/decor-onion.png" alt="" loading="lazy"/></div><section class="mb-20 px-5 pb-9 pt-5 md:px-3 lg:p-16 lg:px-20 relative z-10 bg-fok-sage-500 prose-li:list-none text-fok-navy-500 -mx-5 md:mx-0"><h2 class="mb-7 text-27px font-bold uppercase leading-tight md:text-[40px]">Ingredients</h2><div class="mb-8"><ul class="font-serif leading-7 text-fok-navy-500"><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>1 medium butternut squash (1¾ lb.)</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil (optional, <a href="#h-tips">learn more</a>)</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>1 onion, finely chopped (1 cup)</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>4 cloves garlic, minced</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>½ teaspoon finely chopped fresh thyme</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>1 cup unsweetened, unflavored plant milk</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>2 tablespoons nutritional yeast</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>1 tablespoon white wine vinegar</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>½ teaspoon sea salt</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>⅛ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>3 cups dried whole grain penne pasta (8 oz.)</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>3 cups small broccoli florets</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg"><span>Fresh basil leaves</span></li></ul></div></section><div class="grid grid-cols-12"><div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-7 md:col-start-2"><section class="mb-20 px-5 pb-9 pt-5 md:px-3 lg:p-16 lg:px-20 !p-0"><h2 class="mb-7 text-27px font-bold uppercase leading-tight md:text-[40px]">Instructions</h2><div class="mb-8"><ul class="font-serif leading-7 text-fok-navy-500 list-decimal text-lg"><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg ml-6 pl-3 lg:pl-11 marker:font-sans marker:text-base marker:font-semibold"><span>Peel squash; halve squash and remove seeds. Cut squash into large pieces. Place squash pieces in a steamer basket in a large pan. Add water to saucepan to just below basket. Bring to boiling. Steam, covered, about 12 minutes or until tender.</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg ml-6 pl-3 lg:pl-11 marker:font-sans marker:text-base marker:font-semibold"><span>For oil-free: Heat a medium saucepan over medium. Add onion, garlic, thyme, and ¼ cup water to pan. Cook about 6 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring occasionally and adding water, 1 to 2 tablespoons. at a time, as needed to prevent sticking. <em>(If using oil: In a medium saucepan, heat olive oil, then add onion, garlic, and thyme. Cook about 6 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.)</em></span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg ml-6 pl-3 lg:pl-11 marker:font-sans marker:text-base marker:font-semibold"><span>Transfer onion mixture to a blender. Add squash and the next five ingredients (through pepper). Cover and blend until smooth. Pour squash mixture into a large saucepan.</span></li><li class="mb-2.5 text-base lg:text-lg ml-6 pl-3 lg:pl-11 marker:font-sans marker:text-base marker:font-semibold"><span>Cook pasta according to package directions, adding broccoli the last 5 minutes of cooking; drain. Add drained pasta and broccoli to squash mixture; toss to coat. Serve warm topped with fresh basil.</span></li></ul></div></section><div class="not-prose mb-14"><div class="font-sans font-bold uppercase">Nutritional Information:</div><p class="mb-2 font-sans">Per serving (2 cups): 490 calories, 104 g carbohydrates, 22 g protein, 5 g total fat, 0 g saturated fat, 0 g cholesterol, 651 mg sodium, 10 g fiber, 12 g sugar</p><p class="font-sans"><strong>Note:</strong> Nutritional information is provided as an estimate only.</p></div><div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-7 md:col-start-2"><div class="not-prose my-8 flex flex-col items-baseline text-sm uppercase md:mb-0"><strong class="title mr-1">tags:</strong><ul class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline"><li class="w-max"><a class="font-bold text-[#999] hover:text-fok-teal-600" href="/tag/30-minutes-or-less/" rel="tag">30 minutes or less</a></li></ul></div><section id="comments-section"><div class="my-7 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:gap-10"><h2 class="not-prose my-0 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[27px] font-bold uppercase text-fok-navy-500">Comments<!-- --> <span class="text-[0.48em] font-normal tracking-[1.2px]">(<!-- -->125<!-- -->)</span></h2><div class="flex items-center !text-fok-navy-500"><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 !my-0 !pl-0"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><span class="ml-2 flex text-[13px] uppercase leading-[21px] tracking-[1.2px]">(5 from 67 votes)</span></div></div><div data-orientation="vertical"><div data-state="open" data-orientation="vertical" class="border-y border-y-[#ccd3d8] py-18px"><button type="button" aria-controls="radix-:R6muqcddbm:" aria-expanded="true" data-state="open" data-orientation="vertical" id="radix-:R2muqcddbm:" class="w-full text-left" data-radix-collection-item=""><span class="accordionTriggerChevron relative flex cursor-pointer items-center gap-2.5 font-sans text-base font-bold uppercase leading-tight tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-teal-600 transition-colors duration-300 hover:text-fok-teal-500">Add a comment and/or rating<svg class="MuiSvgIcon-root MuiSvgIcon-fontSizeMedium transition-transform duration-300 css-vubbuv" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 24 24" data-testid="ExpandMoreIcon"><path d="M16.59 8.59 12 13.17 7.41 8.59 6 10l6 6 6-6z"></path></svg></span></button><div data-state="open" id="radix-:R6muqcddbm:" role="region" aria-labelledby="radix-:R2muqcddbm:" data-orientation="vertical" class="accordionContent py-2.5 [&amp;_form]:border-b-0" style="--radix-accordion-content-height:var(--radix-collapsible-content-height);--radix-accordion-content-width:var(--radix-collapsible-content-width)"><form class="mb-11 border-b border-b-[#ccd3d8] pb-5 pt-3"><div class="mb-8 flex items-center gap-4"><p class="!mb-0 !mt-1 font-sans uppercase tracking-ludicrous">Recipe Rating</p><div class="flex gap-1"><div class="flex" role="radio" aria-checked="false" tabindex="0" aria-label="Rating 1 out of 5"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></div><div class="flex" role="radio" aria-checked="false" tabindex="0" aria-label="Rating 2 out of 5"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></div><div class="flex" role="radio" aria-checked="false" tabindex="0" aria-label="Rating 3 out of 5"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></div><div class="flex" role="radio" aria-checked="false" tabindex="0" aria-label="Rating 4 out of 5"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></div><div class="flex" role="radio" aria-checked="false" tabindex="0" aria-label="Rating 5 out of 5"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></div></div><input type="hidden" name="rating" value="0"/></div><label for="comment-field-main" class="form-label">Comment</label><textarea class="form-input mb-8 block h-[203px] min-h-[150px]" id="comment-field-main" name="comment" cols="67" rows="7" placeholder="Write your review or comment here…"></textarea><label for="name-field-main" class="form-label">Name *</label><input type="text" name="author" class="form-input mb-8" id="name-field-main" required=""/><label for="email-field-main" class="form-label">Email *</label><input type="email" name="email" class="form-input mb-8" id="email-field-main" required=""/><p class="mb-41px mb-10 mt-[-1.375rem] text-14px tracking-[1.72]">Your email address will not be published. Required fields are marked *</p><div class="flex gap-5"><button type="submit" class="m-0 flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap bg-fok-teal-blue-400 px-5 pb-17px pt-19px text-center font-sans text-15px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-slighter text-fok-navy-500 transition-colors duration-300 hover:bg-fok-teal-blue-500 hover:text-white disabled:opacity-90 disabled:hover:bg-fok-teal-blue-400">Submit</button><button type="reset" class="m-0 flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap px-5 pb-17px pt-19px text-center font-sans text-15px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-slighter text-fok-teal-blue-400 transition-colors duration-300 hover:bg-fok-teal-blue-400 hover:text-white">Cancel</button></div></form></div></div></div><div class="comments-container"><div class="pb-6" id="comment-78629"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Jerrie</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-11-11T00:20:11.000Z">6 months ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-78629" aria-label="Reply to Jerrie">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Had absolutely no flavour. FOK recipes I&#x27;ve tried so far have been fantastic but this was a definite miss.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-76997"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Maria</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-04-15T13:23:26.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-76997" aria-label="Reply to Maria">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I did not read the comments before making this recipe.  Saying that, I made a few adjustments such as I added the cubed butternut squash after sautéing the onion, garlic and thyme, I left it in the pan, covered until the squash was almost tender, then I uncovered the pan and allowed the liquid to evaporate until there was only about half a cupful or so of liquid left in the pan. (Even if you steam the squash, it still contains a lot of liquid.)  Then added all the other ingredients and used a stick blender.  I thought it was a good sauce recipe.  You can add more ingredients and have as a soup if you wanted to, just add some stock and roasted red peppers from a jar,  pinch of cayenne pepper and a little smoked paprika before blending and serve with a swirl of vegan natural yogurt. I found the sauce to be thick enough to coat the pasta. I gave mine a swirl of sriracha once served in the dish.  I think this is a nice recipe. I do have plenty of sauce left so I will use with spaghetti and maybe add peas too. It’s easy to adapt to your own liking - thank you for the recipe. </p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75419"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Anne</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-28T00:23:34.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75419" aria-label="Reply to Anne">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This was so, so bland even though I added garlic powder, onion powder, tons of red pepper flakes, and more salt. Just not a great flavor and my palate is quite accustomed to WFPB diet so can&#x27;t blame that! I wish I&#x27;d read some of the suggestions beforehand, I really don&#x27;t think I&#x27;ll try it again (no one in my family could even finish one serving). I do agree with some comments that I&#x27;d rather use one of my go-to fake queso recipes and just add pasta and broccoli.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75363"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Sandy</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-23T20:06:59.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75363" aria-label="Reply to Sandy">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I had more sauce than needed, so I added oat milk because I was out of almond milk and some white mayo and a drizzle of maple syrup and made a soup soup out of the leftover sauce. It was pretty good.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75355"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Deborah W</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-23T04:00:07.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75355" aria-label="Reply to Deborah W">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I just made this.  It’s delicious but needed more nutritional yeast &amp;amp; salt. </p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75339"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Linda Watkins</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-21T23:14:09.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75339" aria-label="Reply to Linda Watkins">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I only had Oat milk, and the sauce was very watery. Not sure if 2 cups was too much or if it was the consistency of oat milk. But what a great recipe! I also used Garbanzo Bean Macaroni for more protein.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75333"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">DD</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-21T14:53:31.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75333" aria-label="Reply to DD">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Someone stated in a post that they make oat yogurt. I would love to have a recipes for that if you would not mind sharing.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75330"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Mary Beth Johnson</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-21T04:10:15.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75330" aria-label="Reply to Mary Beth Johnson">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Is it possible to leave out the nutritional yeast?</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75324"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">SJ</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-20T22:40:39.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75324" aria-label="Reply to SJ">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">After reading all the comments, I was nervous of the sweetness factor.  Instead I added half a roasted acorn squash to the Forks Over Knives Queso https://www.forksoverknives.com/recipes/vegan-sauces-condiments/vegan-queso-sauce/  It was good.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75322"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Joyce</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-20T18:49:44.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75322" aria-label="Reply to Joyce">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Thank you for your recipe. I know when I started eating a WFPB diet it was hard as there wasn’t the junk in it and but I felt better after eating it. Because it’s real food. I would like to encourage others to adjust the recipe to suit your taste buds and sharing your additions to help others stay on the path of healthier eating. 
As Chef John says, “you’ll be the winner of how you make your own dinner”. </p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75311"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Marilyn Kircus</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-20T17:17:47.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75311" aria-label="Reply to Marilyn Kircus">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I made this with silken tofu plus just enough soy milk to get it to thr consistency I wanted. I thought it was too bland, so added 2 tablespoons of white miso and a bit of liquid smoke, as well as smoked paprika and lemon juice and cider. 

It was so delicious, that I ate some with crackers and some mixed  with tomato salsa and tortilla chips chips. I will make batches of this to then serve in various ways. I cooked chickpea pasta to up my protein when I ate it as intended. </p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75310"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Rachel</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-20T16:55:46.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75310" aria-label="Reply to Rachel">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I&#x27;ve not made this recipe yet but wanted to read the comments/suggestions before doing so. Lots of folks mentioned it being too sweet and not savory enough. A suggestion is to consider adding store-bought &quot;poultry seasoning&quot; which is a mixture of spices that add savory flavors. One can also add Better Than Bouillon to deepen the flavoring: https://www.betterthanbouillon.com/products/seasoned-vegetable-base/?srsltid=AfmBOoqkM-o3FPPwIPgZhQm1W7ZTcmIf8ABcoy9BkN8UkoU8Gf5dYVU_

Better Than Bouillon also has an entire line of vegan/vegetarian bouillon flavorings:  https://www.betterthanbouillon.com/our-products/?group=vegetarian
They can be high in salt but they also have low salt versions of some products. 
I am not affiliated with them, just want to share some helpful tips.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75309"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Paul</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-20T16:38:11.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75309" aria-label="Reply to Paul">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">You did not have to give a one star though. I thought that was kind of cheesy. Someone was nice enough to share a recipe. </p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75280"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Nancy</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-19T05:10:26.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75280" aria-label="Reply to Nancy">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I’m going to be completely honest, although I’ve only been on the plant-based diet for only two weeks now. This recipe was super tough for me. I tried to spruce up the “butternut cheese sauce” by adding more white wine vinegar, salt, and nutritional yeast. But it just didn’t do it for me. I couldn’t even finish the meal. I’ve seen other recipes where people have used nuts like cashews and water and mixed it into a blender, so I’m going to try that as a “cheese sauce” next. Super sad, this one just didn’t do it for me. I also don’t have a sweet tooth so the sweetness from the butternut squash was too over powering for me. Thank you for the thoughtful recipe but my taste buds did not enjoy this unfortunately</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-75314"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">VeggieT8r</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2025-01-20T17:58:02.000Z">1 year ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I also don&#x27;t have a sweet tooth and found the sweetness off-putting for mac and &quot;cheese&quot;.  I loved the idea and texture though, so I tried various modifications to cut the sweetness.  Adding more acid (lemon juice or vinegar) didn&#x27;t work for me at all, and I even tried lactic acid powder.  Blending in a handful of cashews helped some, but I sure don&#x27;t need all those extra calories.  Another time I had a half can of white beans in the fridge I needed to use, and a bag of already steamed yellow potatoes, so I tossed the beans and a few little potatoes into the blender along with the other ingredients, and added a big dollop of homemade oat yogurt and a small squirt of dijon, which both cut and masked the sweetness. Suited my tastes much better.  
I get why recipes trying to stand-in for forbidden favorites are named after them, but I also think getting set up for the expectation of same is usually pretty disappointing.  I really do like butternut squash, but not as an imposter for &quot;cheese&quot;;  there are other sauces I prefer for that.  This is one of them right here... https://www.forksoverknives.com/recipes/vegan-sauces-condiments/vegan-queso-sauce/</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-75010"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Amy</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2024-12-28T23:08:08.000Z">1 year ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-75010" aria-label="Reply to Amy">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">..searching for vegan recipe for a long time…I will never cook regular Mac and cheese again this is so good with broccoli! Thank you for this recipe!! ..reduced the salt and sub yeast with coconut amino acid. </p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-74411"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Jan</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2024-11-04T22:06:07.000Z">2 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-74411" aria-label="Reply to Jan">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I made this after reviewing the comments. Only used 1 cup of almond milk. Perfect consistency. I also roasted the squash in the oven (with some garlic powder)  as opposed to steaming it. Great flavor. I did not find it to be too sweet. A great recipe with some minor tweaks.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-74147"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">D. Doyne</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2024-10-09T20:18:28.000Z">2 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-74147" aria-label="Reply to D. Doyne">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I made this today and it was delicious! I used unsweetened almond milk.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-73103"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Kate</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2024-07-01T15:59:34.000Z">2 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-73103" aria-label="Reply to Kate">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">love love love this recipe. Highly recommend reading the comments for lots of ideas for variations</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-71930"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">C Powell</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2024-02-24T03:44:28.000Z">2 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-71930" aria-label="Reply to C Powell">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I used Kabocha squash and one cup of milk omitted the vinegar. Add extra nutritional yeast. It was very delicious. Add milk as needed 😋 </p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-71844"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Teresa</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2024-02-16T00:48:40.000Z">2 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-71844" aria-label="Reply to Teresa">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This was wayyyy too sweet. We felt like we were eating “pudding pasta.” My son loved it, but my husband and I had to muscle through it. Won’t be making this again. </p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-71402"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Genie</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2024-01-13T23:38:07.000Z">2 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-71402" aria-label="Reply to Genie">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I make this often.  I use a 12 ounce package of frozen butternut squash cubes (I cut the recipe in half for the two of us), and add mushrooms.  The thyme didn’t do it for me so I use curry powder instead.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-71182"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Marry</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-12-29T16:37:54.000Z">2 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-71182" aria-label="Reply to Marry">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">My changes include add half the amount of milk, roast a Kuri squash, roast a head of garlic and the best part: stir in roasted walnuts just before serving.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-70808"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">AllergyCity</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-11-25T02:26:46.000Z">2 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-70808" aria-label="Reply to AllergyCity">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Can I make this without yeast and vinegar? Thanks!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-70531"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Rebecca Waldron-Geranis</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-11-05T13:30:00.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-70531" aria-label="Reply to Rebecca Waldron-Geranis">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Yummy, but too soupy! I would add only one cup of milk instead of two. I used a whole box 12oz. of Jovial GF fusilli which has been the best GF pasta I have found to date. Of course I added a little extra salt and pepper! I wonder about putting some chili flakes for a little heat. Maybe next time!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-70513"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Granny K</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-11-04T17:51:25.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-70513" aria-label="Reply to Granny K">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">What a great recipe!  Used frozen sweet potatoes, two 10 oz bags, cooked in microwave for recommended time.  Everything else followed as written.  Used julienned snow peas   instead of broccoli, and love, love, love this recipe!  I prefer this Mac and “cheese” version over the cashew one.  I’m really loving learning to cook all over again with fok!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-69995"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Jill</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-09-21T22:28:53.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-69995" aria-label="Reply to Jill">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Found this recipe to be disappointing. Read the other reviews that were helpful, but the butternut squash was too sweet. It tasted better the next day, but I will not make this again.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-69466"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Fatima Delgado</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-07-31T11:20:47.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-69466" aria-label="Reply to Fatima Delgado">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Delicious!! I added one more table spoon of nutritional yeast and instrad of broccoli i used spinach and extra garlic its delicious and healthy!!</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-69962"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Gabriella Durango</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-09-17T20:18:46.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This is a great recipe, but I highly recommend you use kabocha or kuri squash instead.  Kuri squash in particular has a lovely creamy consistency that will make for a better sauce. Also, if you have time to roast the squash instead of boil, I think it tastes better. I roasted my squash, added it to cashew milk as it was heating in a saucepan,  mashed it (an immersion blender works well here), till it was to my liking. Also start with less milk than you think you&#x27;ll need and add more as you go.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-68882"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Paul Simpson Sr</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-06-10T13:48:38.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-68882" aria-label="Reply to Paul Simpson Sr">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">My son made it for me and it was great!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-68607"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Kate</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-05-16T11:23:22.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-68607" aria-label="Reply to Kate">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Why won&#x27;t this recipe print or any of the recipes from the email received from FOKs dated May 13, 2023 @ 11:08.
&quot;MOST POPULAR FOK RECIPES
OUR TOP 25 FAN-FAVORITES&quot;?</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-68526"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Esther</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-05-09T22:42:54.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-68526" aria-label="Reply to Esther">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I used doubled the yeast and added vegetable stock tablets for a more &quot;cheesy&quot; taste, I also put the blended mixture back in a pot on the oven to thicken a little before adding the pasta and broccoli, it tastes great.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-68330"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Amanda L</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-04-24T09:38:32.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-68330" aria-label="Reply to Amanda L">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">After reading the other reviews, I only added 1 cup of oat milk. That have me perfect clingy texture. It was a little sweet but after adding extra salt and pepper it was good. I&#x27;m at the beginning of my wfpb journey so hopefully after my taste buds adjust I won&#x27;t need so much salt.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-68161"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Whit</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-04-11T16:48:24.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-68161" aria-label="Reply to Whit">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">So yummy. I didn’t realize we were out of broccoli until it was time to add it, so I used spinach instead. It was great.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-67753"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Linda Aikey</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-03-12T19:03:03.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-67753" aria-label="Reply to Linda Aikey">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">When I have too much of a soupy version I add some oatmeal, perhaps a cup ground in food processor. Then because of it being mac and cheese, more nutritional yeast. Then I sprinkle to taste between 1/8 to 1/4 tsp: sea salt, garlic powder, onion powder, turmeric, ginger, curry, dry mustard, paprika, cumin and cayenne pepper. Lemon juice works for me too. It zings up the taste buds.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-67754"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Linda Aikey</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-03-12T19:10:38.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">If you try this recipe again, add a sweet potato and perhaps less squash. The touch of sweetness is really nice.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-67691"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Arturo</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-03-09T18:36:53.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-67691" aria-label="Reply to Arturo">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">BeautifuL!!! Thank you!! </p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-67705"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Brian Rogers</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-03-10T09:22:31.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Anyone know the calorie count for this?</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-66848"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Casey</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-01-21T18:45:49.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-66848" aria-label="Reply to Casey">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This recipe definitely didn&#x27;t do it for me. I don&#x27;t know why I keep expecting miracles from vegan recipes. This did not taste cheesy at all. It&#x27;s my first time using nutritional yeast as a &quot;cheesy&quot; substitute and I&#x27;ll probably never use it again.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-67114"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Dena O’Neill</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-02-04T12:19:15.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I’m finding the recipes on this site bland as well. There’s a lot of vegan Mac n cheese out there that are super tasty. Just don’t expect them to taste exactly like cheese. Keep searching!</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-67121"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Lou</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-02-04T15:24:42.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I always add Franks hot sauce- you can’t go wrong (I put that $h*t on everything)</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-67134"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Margarita Crupe</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-02-04T23:26:42.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Violife Parmesan cheese is a great substitute for nutritional yeast.  You could purchase it at Fresh Thyme in your area.  Substituting the white wine vinegar with fresh lemon juice gives it a clean and fresh taste.  At times when I find a recipe, I tweak it with flavors I like.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-67727"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Thea Lesnik</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-03-11T12:53:39.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Keep trying :) I find it gets better and better as your taste buds get a custom to good food :)</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-67740"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Patti</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-03-12T08:15:17.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I&#x27;m a part time vegan but 2 of my kids are plus 2 grand kids. I&#x27;ve found the Non Fortified nutritional yeast is by far the best tasting. The fortified has B vitamins added and yuck, it&#x27;s awful. 
Plus I don&#x27;t call it cheese or Mac n cheese. For my non vegans this conjures up a certain look and taste. I just call it creamy pasta.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-66188"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Lorraine</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-12-14T16:09:05.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-66188" aria-label="Reply to Lorraine">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Used 1 1/2 cups of almond milk instead of 2. Perfect consistency and delicious!!
Thank you for this recipe!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-65850"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Elsa</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-27T17:03:51.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-65850" aria-label="Reply to Elsa">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Was pretty good. Took others comments into account and added more nutritional yeast, used lemon juice instead of vinegar, added some hot sauce, used leeks instead of onion, but still a bit bland and soupy. Added some chopped Kale with broccoli. Needs something else.....</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-65865"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Chili Dave</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-28T17:37:16.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">It was pretty good.  I did add more nutritional yeast and hot sauce.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-69106"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Em</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-06-28T17:05:35.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Nutmeg and cayenne</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-65831"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Beth</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-27T04:33:20.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-65831" aria-label="Reply to Beth">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">How many cups of cubed squash would that be?</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-65820"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Joanne</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-26T10:57:22.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-65820" aria-label="Reply to Joanne">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Can i substitute nutritional yeast or leave out all together?</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-65814"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Gail Fuson</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-26T09:15:57.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-65814" aria-label="Reply to Gail Fuson">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Why can these recipes not be printable</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-65817"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Ralph</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-26T10:25:27.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">It is. At the top of the article is a print/save button. Click on that and it will open it as a pdf. Hold your curser near the bottom of the page and a little box with four options should open. The last, the down arrow, is the download button. Click that and download to your desktop or downloads folder. (I&#x27;m using safari but it works in Chrome browser too. In Chrome in the new window that opens, the download button is the down arrow at the top of the screen.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-65818"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Jasmine</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-26T10:26:09.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">That’s always annoying!  They are printable from the app at least</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-65819"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Ralph</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-26T10:28:49.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">And to print, in the new screen that opens, in Chrome there should be a print button and in Safari go to File at the very top of the browser bar, click that and then click print</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-65836"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Doireann</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-27T08:09:39.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Agreed.  It&#x27;s ridiculous.

As to the suggestion in a reply to your comment, using the file&amp;gt;print function (at least in Safari) results in a ridiculously wonky printout with giant empty spaces, overlapping type, instructions cut off or left out, and having to figure out which pages you need because otherwise it will print the entire webpage (upwards of 30 pages of paper).</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-65837"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Candace Lamoree</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-27T08:33:00.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">There is a print recipe option at the top of the recipe.  I just saved it as a pdf.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-67103"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Janine</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-02-04T07:17:55.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">It’s printable- select print/save, then open in browser, then print like you would from your phone</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-65749"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Peggy</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-22T10:43:42.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-65749" aria-label="Reply to Peggy">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Because my husband and I will be attending a Thanksgiving dinner and we are now plant-based, I&#x27;ll be trying this recipe to bring for us.  Glad I read all of the other comments as it&#x27;ll give me a better idea for what to add and what to change.  THANKS!</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-66061"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Sammie J</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-12-09T18:37:07.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">MAKE IT 2 WEEKS BEFORE, this is not a one and done! See comments about soupy and bland.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-65682"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Steve</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-18T05:59:20.000Z">3 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-65682" aria-label="Reply to Steve">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Made this last night using suggestions by other commenters.  Doubled up on the nutritional yeast and only used one cup of milk.  Added hot sauce and some Taijin seasoning.  It tasted pretty darn good.  I&#x27;d make it again.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-65200"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Steph</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-10-19T18:33:12.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-65200" aria-label="Reply to Steph">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">THIS is so delicious! Honestly, I was doubtful but wow was I 100% wrong. I will definitely prepare this again!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-64958"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Ami Ross</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-10-05T14:55:24.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-64958" aria-label="Reply to Ami Ross">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I followed the directions exactly, and it was WAY too soupy. Any suggestions for thickening it up so this whole batch isn’t wasted?  Thank you.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-65242"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Julia</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-10-22T20:12:53.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">You can always add flour to the sauce.  There&#x27;s also either cornstarch or arrowroot powder.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-66902"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Mandy</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-01-24T10:29:14.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Just add more nutritional yeast. I put 6-8 tablespoons in my “cheese” sauces, along with plenty of sea salt, black pepper, a teaspoon of Miso, a heaped tsp or two of onion and garlic granules. For extra richness you can also add some soya cream (i use Alpro or Oatly).</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-64596"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Susan Packwood</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-09-11T16:19:04.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-64596" aria-label="Reply to Susan Packwood">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Good!  Really needed more salt and mine was a little too soupy .  But I used peas instead of broccoli which would have taken up more volume.  But I love butternut squash, so I loved the taste.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-64711"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Amy</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-09-19T17:58:51.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Trying it, looks good.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-64488"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Debbie</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-09-02T17:09:30.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-64488" aria-label="Reply to Debbie">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I really enjoyed this meal, and will make it again. As others stated, it was a bit bland. I did what one suggested and doubled the Nutritional Yeast. Then when I heated it to eat again, I sprinkled more Nutrtional Yeast, Onion Powder, and Thyme.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-65273"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">JC</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-10-24T20:37:06.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Pretty good! Play with the seasoning to ensure you get it right. I added a little crushed red pepper for some heat and a lot more “nooch”. I also added sage. That helped.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-64017"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">DiAne</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-08-02T09:56:34.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-64017" aria-label="Reply to DiAne">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Have been wanting to find a good vegan mac and cheese recipe and this fills the spot. Easy to prepare. I used acorn squash as that is what I had on hand. It all came together so easily.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-62837"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Karole</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-05-16T18:37:05.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-62837" aria-label="Reply to Karole">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">What are nutrients values?</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-62759"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Connie Reilly</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-05-14T11:12:38.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-62759" aria-label="Reply to Connie Reilly">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Can you use Yellow summer squash?</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-62937"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Betty</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-05-23T17:09:52.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">They are two different types of squash so I&#x27;m not certain that would be a good substitute.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-64716"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">D&#x27;Awn</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-09-20T12:12:25.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">As a southern gal who grew up on yellow summer squash, I&#x27;d say no. The water content in summer squash is much higher than in winter squash.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-62057"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Josa Mendoza</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-03-29T17:05:05.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-62057" aria-label="Reply to Josa Mendoza">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">OK this was really good. I did doctor it up a little bit though, I didn’t have any plant-based milk so I used a can of coconut cream. Everything else was pretty much the same I also added the franks hot sauce like some of the other readers commented. I will make this again.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-61577"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Carol</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-03-01T18:07:27.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-61577" aria-label="Reply to Carol">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Beautiful - the colors are radiant.  I love Broccoli, I love Butternut Squash, and I Love Pasta!  I am in the third week of a 6 week juice fast and I am adding this recipe to the list of those I will be making after my cleanse is over.
Thank you for posting it!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-60981"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Sarah</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-02-01T13:35:03.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-60981" aria-label="Reply to Sarah">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I made this to bring to work and I like it. Added a little extra nutritional yeast and vinegar. The basil really makes it for me. I&#x27;m going to add chickpeas and eat it with a side of broccoli when I go to work.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-61578"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Carol</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-03-01T18:09:59.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I like your addition of chickpeas!  When I make it I may add sweet peas, too, or maybe 1 inch cuts of steamed fresh green beans.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-65812"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Sharon</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-11-26T06:27:37.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Chick peas is the move!Oh and playing with the spices.  I like coconut and oat milk but someone suggested coconut cream.  That’s what I used. Very good!  Great recipe!!! Glad I bought that squash even though I decided not to make what I’d planned.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-60973"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Maja</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-02-01T08:54:31.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-60973" aria-label="Reply to Maja">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I was looking forward to try this recipe, but I must say I&#x27;m disappointed. The dish was way too bland, I was hoping for a deeper, more cheezy taste.Maybe with less milk and more nutritional yeast it would be better. But it definitely needs something to spice it up.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-60958"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Deb</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-01-31T18:42:21.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-60958" aria-label="Reply to Deb">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Thank you for this recipe. I wanted to try this because I love squash. It wasn&#x27;t a fantastic dish but it wasn&#x27;t bad either. It definitely needs some extra spice. I added some garlic powder,  onion powder, and next time maybe some veggie broth while cooking the onions instead of water. I used the whole wheat elbows which is new for me also, getting used to that flavor. (my kids don&#x27;t like the wheat pastas). It made a lot for just me eating it so I froze some hoping it will be good later. I&#x27;m new to plant based eating but open to try most any recipe.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-60671"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Wilhelm van Greunen</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-01-21T10:52:40.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-60671" aria-label="Reply to Wilhelm van Greunen">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I made this and it was super delicious! I will definitely add it to my plant-based recipe collection. I used about 800g of cubed butternut (we use the metric system in Namibia where I&#x27;m from), and my sauce had the perfect consistency and clung to the pasta very well.u</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-60644"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Valerie Russell</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-01-19T23:32:33.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-60644" aria-label="Reply to Valerie Russell">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Very tasty recipe. I roasted the cubed butternut squash instead of steaming it, and used oat milk. Yes, it is very saucy, but it is yummy squash puree, so all is forgiven.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-60523"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Elizabeth Conley</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-01-15T17:07:34.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-60523" aria-label="Reply to Elizabeth Conley">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Best vegan Mac and cheese recipe I&#x27;ve made so far. It made alot of sauce. Next time I&#x27;ll make twice as much pasta I think. A little bland but nothing some hot sauce couldn&#x27;t fix</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-59414"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Jane</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-11-26T07:39:28.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-59414" aria-label="Reply to Jane">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I don&#x27;t think I&#x27;ll make this again. The sauce was grainy and didn&#x27;t cover the pasta, just sunk down to the bottom. I also had to add more seasoning.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-59268"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">edith</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-11-20T06:42:36.000Z">4 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-59268" aria-label="Reply to edith">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I love pasta, mac and cheese and broccoli, but I really don&#x27;t like squash. And sub suggestions or is it a bust for me?</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-59279"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Anna</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-11-20T09:45:03.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">It works well with sweet potato and potato mix or just sweet potato. Carrot might work too.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-59092"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Diane Cutler</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-11-13T09:48:24.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-59092" aria-label="Reply to Diane Cutler">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">We love this recipe. I didn’t have broccoli so I used carrots instead and it is so good. We will be having this again and again. I have also shared it with other, even if they are not plant based.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-59057"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">K Boyd</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-11-11T15:39:29.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-59057" aria-label="Reply to K Boyd">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This is not my favorite FoK recipe. I added lots more vegetables and some hot sauce.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-58891"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Linda</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-11-02T06:35:31.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-58891" aria-label="Reply to Linda">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Tasty and easy! I made a few modifications based on the reviews. I reduced the amount of oat milk to 1 cup, used a jar of pumpkin puree instead of butternut squash (lazy weeknight!), substituted lemon juice for the vinegar, and also roasted the onion, garlic, and broccoli in the oven. I topped the pasta with toasted pine nuts, a spring of rosemary, and chopped red chilis which added a nice spice. I&#x27;ll definitely make this one again.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-58932"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Sparti</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-11-04T09:15:59.000Z">5 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Thanks for this review and all your tips! I’m going to try your suggestions :)</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-59278"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Carol</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-11-20T09:28:24.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Linda, what size can of pumpkin puree did you use?  Thanks!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-58334"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Christina</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-10-04T06:10:16.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-58334" aria-label="Reply to Christina">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Easy to make and quite surprisingly creamy. It won&#x27;t replace exactly the flavour of what you expect from a mac and cheese but enjoying it as an alternative and being open to trying something different, this delivers! It was a bit on the sweet side so I added a little more white wine vinegar and some miso paste. A tasty and healthy alternative to a comforting dish. We will definitely make again!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-57788"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Francine Shogel</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-09-05T16:21:47.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-57788" aria-label="Reply to Francine Shogel">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">It was delicious! Made a lot of sauce, so asking if can be frozen?</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-57770"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">GP</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-09-04T15:19:32.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-57770" aria-label="Reply to GP">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Not made but will try for sure...could I sub low fat COCONUT milk/cream?</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-62829"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">cathleen morris</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-05-16T15:55:20.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">The sauce was sweet and an unusual taste… I added a bit of Frank’s hot sauce to counteract but ultimately I ended up adding tomato sauce and it was actually very good, just not a Mac n cheese dish</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-57544"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">EH</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-08-27T06:30:59.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-57544" aria-label="Reply to EH">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">As someone who didn&#x27;t grow up with mac and cheese I really had no expectations and found this recipe to be better than anticipated (only roughly stuck to the proportions given though). The sauce was creamy and extremely filling (had it over leftover rice and steamed vegetables) and I didn&#x27;t mind the sweet taste of the butternut squash. I substituted the plant milk with a couple of teaspoons of cashew butter and water. Next time I will use lemon juice instead of vinegar. Thyme wasn&#x27;t at hand. Nutmeg might be good in this recipe. The only thing I didn&#x27;t enjoy so much about this sauce was the oniony aftertaste due to the onions being cooked rather than fried/sautéed.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-56836"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">MB</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-08-23T08:13:02.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-56836" aria-label="Reply to MB">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Wouldn’t normally take the time to comment but this was delicious! Will add more yeast and add salt at the table to taste. Creamy and nourishing!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-55457"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Tina</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-08-14T14:55:06.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-55457" aria-label="Reply to Tina">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This tastes delicious! Added less plant-based milk because it would have been too much. Was still plenty!</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-60961"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Colleen</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2022-01-31T22:37:39.000Z">4 years ago</time></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I didn’t know what to expect out of this but it was better than I thought. I, like others, added more spice as I felt it was a bit bland. I also added more pasta too to have a better pasta/sauce ratio.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-52274"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Sharon</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-07-25T08:21:00.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-52274" aria-label="Reply to Sharon">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Sadly, this recipe didn&#x27;t do it for me. Even with unsweetened milked, this meal tasted sweet and not savory. Also, it might be helpful to suggested squash quantity rather than &quot;medium&quot; as it I felt like there was too much squash. 

I am never a fan when I have to throw out food (grew up in a family where this was a practically a sin), but this meal could not be eatened.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-57839"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Marlo</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-09-09T07:44:36.000Z">5 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I’ve made this recipe many times. Delicious!</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-58084"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Kris</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-09-21T15:52:49.000Z">5 years ago</time></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">New to this, I knew it wasn&#x27;t going to be what I&#x27;m used to, but I do love my veggies. I felt it had way too much onion in it. Towards the end of my bowl, that&#x27;s all I tasted. I also think it needs another seasoning added to it.
Other than that, it was very healthy.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-58087"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Peg</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-09-21T18:58:32.000Z">5 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Wayyyy too much milk in this recipe. It came out more like squash soup with pasta and broccoli in it. That said, it was tasty. I would just use about half the amount of milk next time.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-52224"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Geana a Johnson</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-07-24T10:53:57.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-52224" aria-label="Reply to Geana a Johnson">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Love butternut squash.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-52181"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Candice</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-07-24T06:45:44.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-52181" aria-label="Reply to Candice">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This was simple to make but the flavor was a little too sweet for the family.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-55050"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Sharyn</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-08-11T15:06:59.000Z">5 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">How many calories does this have per serving?</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-50732"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">CJ</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-07-15T21:24:20.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-50732" aria-label="Reply to CJ">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-30"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I really wanted to love this! I felt it was too much sauce to pasta ratio and it wasn’t a bold enough flavour for me, maybe with less milk would have been better and more nutritional yeast. Thankyou for the recipe, Nice to give it a try, just wasn’t for me :)</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-50545"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Didi Lacroix</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-07-14T11:42:59.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-50545" aria-label="Reply to Didi Lacroix">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Really yummy! I&#x27;ve made another vegan Mac &amp;amp; cheese before and it was not half as delicious as this one. Great texture as well. And I like that it incorporates broccoli, which includes a green vegetable.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-49640"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Deb Lee</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-07-09T23:30:30.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-49640" aria-label="Reply to Deb Lee">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">When is the vinegar added? I can&#x27;t se it in the instructions.</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-50115"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Hilary Thompson</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-07-13T06:56:56.000Z">5 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">In point 3 the instruction is &quot;add the next five ingredients&quot;, this includes the vinegar. </p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-45737"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Sueathome</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-06-25T09:11:37.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-45737" aria-label="Reply to Sueathome">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I made this and it is divine! I replace vinegar with lemon juice. I never use the yeast. It was superb!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-34994"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Melinda W</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-06-15T14:42:49.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-34994" aria-label="Reply to Melinda W">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This is absolutely delicious!!
Is the nutritional information available?</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-67102"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Gabrielle</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2023-02-04T07:04:36.000Z">3 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Making a roux to mix in with the butter squash will give it more creaminess. I also add nutmeg and a splash of maggi or liquid aminos for a better taste.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-28807"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Angie</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-06-13T22:38:19.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-28807" aria-label="Reply to Angie">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">A very tasty and healthy recipe. Not too complicated to make. Great for taking to work and reheating too.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-18948"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Mary Ciulla</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-05-29T03:32:25.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-18948" aria-label="Reply to Mary Ciulla">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Even when I was not a vegetarian or a vegan I put broccoli, or cauliflower, in my macaroni and cheese.  I can&#x27;t wait to make this!</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-37934"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Kathleen Baas</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-06-16T17:56:36.000Z">5 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Can&#x27;t wait to try this!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-18943"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Corinne Krepel</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-05-28T22:07:35.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-18943" aria-label="Reply to Corinne Krepel">Reply</a></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Wondering if I can use frozen butternut squash??</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-45743"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Sueathome</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-06-25T09:12:28.000Z">5 years ago</time></div></div><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Absolutely</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-13828"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Jennifer</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-04-26T09:31:47.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-13828" aria-label="Reply to Jennifer">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Never thought it would be this good!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-13718"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Jackie Heath</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-04-25T02:18:00.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-13718" aria-label="Reply to Jackie Heath">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">What a lovely,  creamy dish. This dish was very easy to make, and tasted great, I will definitely make this again</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-12596"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Allyson</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-04-19T18:29:17.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-12596" aria-label="Reply to Allyson">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This was delicious! 10/10 will make again!</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-12054"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Marg</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-04-17T21:18:29.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-12054" aria-label="Reply to Marg">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">Yummy comfort food</p></div><div class="pb-6 mb-7 pl-10 pt-5" id="comment-18403"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Dannielle</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-05-24T20:02:38.000Z">5 years ago</time></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">This dish is delicious. I’m the only vegan in my household and getting my husband and kids on board can be a challenge. This dish is a hit with my entire family. Including my father who is a diehard vegan critic</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-11940"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">Donna</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-04-17T08:40:40.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-11940" aria-label="Reply to Donna">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">My kids and I love this!  I use elbow style macaroni and plenty of broccoli.</p></div><div class="pb-6" id="comment-11844"><div class="flex justify-between"><div class="flex items-center gap-5 pb-2.5 text-fok-navy-500"><strong class="text-lg -tracking-veryslight md:text-xl">aram</strong><time class="text-13px uppercase leading-none tracking-[1.2px]" dateTime="2021-04-16T14:06:09.000Z">5 years ago</time></div><div><a rel="nofollow" class="text-13px font-bold uppercase leading-input tracking-[1.5px] text-fok-navy-400 text-opacity-40 md:text-base" href="#comment-11844" aria-label="Reply to aram">Reply</a></div></div><ul class="flex md:gap-x-1 my-2.5"><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li><li class="m-0 flex p-0"><span class="icon-star text-[21px] text-fok-teal-600 opacity-100"></span></li></ul><p class="whitespace-break-spaces break-words font-serif text-base leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] text-fok-navy-500 md:text-lg">I have no idea why broccoli is so good with cheese but it is - and that nutritional yeast always gives food a nice cheesy flavor!</p></div></div></section></div></div><aside class="col-span-12 mb-20 flex flex-col items-center max-md:pt-20 md:col-span-3 md:col-start-10 lg:mb-0"></aside></div></section></div></article><section><div class="mb-6 grid grid-cols-12 bg-fok-sage-500 py-10 max-md:px-4 md:mb-20 container blog:max-w-screen-blog"><p class="col-span-12 mb-2.5 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-fok-teal-600 max-md:text-center max-md:text-13px md:hidden">About the Author</p><div class="col-span-12 flex items-center justify-center px-4 max-md:mb-10 md:col-span-4 [&amp;&gt;picture]:aspect-square"><picture><source srcSet="https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/Darshana-Thacker-732x506-1.jpg?dpr=1&amp;format=auto&amp;optimize=high&amp;width=220 1x, https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/Darshana-Thacker-732x506-1.jpg?dpr=1.5&amp;format=auto&amp;optimize=high&amp;width=220 1.5x, https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/Darshana-Thacker-732x506-1.jpg?dpr=2&amp;format=auto&amp;optimize=high&amp;width=220 2x, https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/Darshana-Thacker-732x506-1.jpg?dpr=3&amp;format=auto&amp;optimize=high&amp;width=220 3x"/><img alt="Headshot of Darshana Thacker" src="https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/Darshana-Thacker-732x506-1.jpg?format=auto&amp;optimize=high&amp;width=1440" class="aspect-square h-full max-w-[220px] rounded-full object-cover"/></picture></div><div class="col-span-12 flex flex-col justify-center text-fok-navy-500 md:col-span-8 md:pr-4"><p class="mb-2.5 text-[13px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-fok-teal-blue-500 max-md:hidden max-md:text-center md:text-base">About the Author</p><h2 class="mb-4 text-17px font-bold uppercase leading-tight tracking-wide max-md:text-center md:text-[27px] md:leading-[1.12]">Darshana Thacker Wendel</h2><div class="mb-6 max-w-[700px] font-serif leading-7 tracking-[0.36px] max-md:text-center md:text-lg">Darshana Thacker Wendel is a whole-food, plant-based chef and former culinary projects manager for Forks Over Knives. A graduate of the Natural Gourmet Institute, she is the author of<a href="https://shop.forksoverknives.com//products/forks-over-knives-flavor"> <em>Forks Over Knives: Flavor!</em></a> She created the recipes for<em><a href="https://shop.forksoverknives.com/products/forks-over-knives-family"> Forks Over Knives Family</a></em> and was a lead recipe contributor to the New York Times bestseller<em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1476753296/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=1476753296&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=forovekni-20"> The Forks Over Knives Plan</a></em>. Her recipes have been published in<em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00JPR5JE6/ref=dp-kindle-redirect?_encoding=UTF8&amp;btkr=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> The Prevent and Reverse Heart Disease Cookbook</a></em>, <em><a href="https://shop.forksoverknives.com/products/forks-over-knives-the-cookbook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Forks Over Knives—The Cookbook</a></em>,<em><a href="https://shop.forksoverknives.com/products/forks-over-knives-the-plant-based-way-to-health"> Forks Over Knives: The Plant-Based Way to Health</a></em>, and LA Yoga magazine online.</div><a class="text-[13px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-fok-teal-600 transition-colors hover:text-fok-navy-500 max-md:text-center md:text-base" href="/contributors/darshana-thacker/">See More from this Author</a></div></div><div class="container mb-10 mt-5 lg:mt-20"><h2 class="mb-5 text-center text-26px font-bold text-fok-navy-500 md:text-34px lg:mb-12 lg:text-40px">MORE FROM FORKS OVER KNIVES</h2><div class="hidden md:block"><div class="MuiBox-root css-cyzz97"><div class="p-1"><div class="MuiBox-root css-f5x0ou"><div class="relative"><a href="/recipes/vegan-breakfast/10-minute-tofu-scrambl